Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    A graph stores nodes such that the distance from a start to end node can be calculated.
    Author:
    Steven Lowes

      • getDistance

      • reset

        Reset the distances to each node to allow them to be recalculated.

      • changeNode

        public boolean changeNode(Coordinate coords,
                          NodeType type,
                          java.lang.Double weight)
                   throws InvalidPositionException
        Change a node at a position, and update all the edges affected by this - meaning that a new graph doesn't have to be created each time you want to test a different board.
        Parameters:
        coords - The coordinates of the node to change
        type - The new type of the node
        weight - The new weight of the node
        Returns:
        boolean indicating successful operation
        Throws:
        InvalidPositionException - The coordinates passed don't represent a node.
